1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
What if I told you that not all research is peer-reviewed?

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:07,600
Preprints are research papers shared before peer review.

3
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:09,600
They spark debate and discovery.

4
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:11,600
But why are they controversial?

5
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,600
Some argue they spread misinformation.

6
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:17,600
Yet, they accelerate scientific progress, allowing immediate feedback and collaboration.

7
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:21,200
So, preprints are a double-edged sword—informative but needing caution.

8
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:24,800
Follow for more insights on science and stay informed!
